    "body": "I was running into this on macOS as well, today.\r\n\r\nFound the solution, after reading the last comment from @cyprienflx \r\nTurns out enabling the \"Set locale as environment variables on startup\" in the Terminal app needs to be enabled:\r\n<img width=\"316\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e540e4b3-763f-4825-9ff8-de81e62d767c\">\r\n\r\nThis option can be found in the Terminal app preferences under Profiles -> Advanced.\r\nAfter enabling the option a restart of the app fixes the wrapping of long commands.",
